Results.ReviewText: I think it would be better to look for other gloves that work with touch devices instead getting of these ones.I live in Denver and I got this coat for the 2-4 days a year that its gets cold enough in Denver to need a really warm coat.I have never been cold in this coat-but I have also only been able to wear this coat around 7 times in 2 years-its just a really warm coat ans if the temp is above 20 F its too warm.\nThe big pockets are nice-my ipad fits inside.

Reacts great and the edges are nice.

The only problem ive had was the binding that were sold to me with the board literally snapped halfway through the baseplate so i had to ride 4 hours with one binding.Overall a great begginner to intermediate board, good choice to buy!i was renting ride boards not sure of type but when i eventually did buy this board i had no idea that it would make that much of a difference ...!! it was simply amazing catching an edge and falling and breaking my tail bone un heard of on this board i love it and would recomend it to anyone buying a board for a first time and interested in freestyle riding even though this board did do it all....!!!!!!

Results.ReviewText:
I've been using it consistently this season over my brown  jacket and this thing is ill.I bought the Geiger in White and I couldn't be more pleased.The inside is nice and silky with the goose down on the inside to keep you warm.The outside looks fresh with a vibrant white with silver logos.

I get compliments on this jacket all the time because of how much it stands out in the crowd.The hood fits perfect over my dragon goggles sitting on top of my head when its not dumping snow.All around this jacket is perfect.

Other than that, it covers your head I guess.This jacket is silky soft, yet durable and waterproof.It has fur in the hood and in patches on your back and overall keeps you just the right amount of warm.

I was not once cold while wearing it.Fits like a glove and moves like a ninja.It looks great on the mountain or off (I got mine in dark blue).I love the thumb strap to keep your sleeves in place - my first experience with this now semi-widespread feature.
